WEBVTT

00:00.700 --> 00:01.980
[Crow caws]

00:02.013 --> 00:04.126
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

00:06.813 --> 00:08.245
Uh-oh. Frosting emergency?

00:08.348 --> 00:10.623
I think you have a back-up can
in the medicine cabinet.

00:10.750 --> 00:12.249
No, I'm looking for something else.

00:12.274 --> 00:14.518
And don't say "back-up can"
like it's a regular thing.

00:14.543 --> 00:15.886
I can stop whenever I want.

00:15.988 --> 00:18.789
Hey, have you seen anything
around the house recently

00:18.814 --> 00:21.025
that looks like I might have hidden it?

00:21.127 --> 00:22.726
[Gasps] Ooh, is it for Dad's birthday?

00:22.828 --> 00:24.128
No, this is for something important.

00:24.230 --> 00:25.870
Axl's graduating in a few weeks,

00:25.895 --> 00:28.032
and I can't find the present I got him.

00:28.134 --> 00:29.733
I was in a store, like, a year ago,

00:29.802 --> 00:31.335
and I stumbled across this thing...

00:31.437 --> 00:33.114
it was touching, it was sentimental,

00:33.139 --> 00:34.805
it was the perfect gift.

00:34.907 --> 00:37.007
So what is it? I don't remember.

00:37.109 --> 00:38.809
I mean, it was like yea big

00:38.911 --> 00:39.957
or yea big.

00:39.982 --> 00:41.078
I don't know.

00:41.180 --> 00:43.487
I threw it in here somewhere, but I...

00:43.512 --> 00:45.349
ooh, my back-up cookies.

00:45.451 --> 00:46.417
Shut up.

00:46.519 --> 00:47.484
It's okay.

00:47.587 --> 00:50.454
So regarding things we can remember,

00:50.556 --> 00:52.089
- what are we doing for Dad's birthday?
- [Scoffs]

00:52.191 --> 00:54.425
I'm not wasting any energy on that guy.

00:54.527 --> 00:56.860
You know he's the least-fun
birthday person ever.

00:56.963 --> 00:58.462
He doesn't want to be sung to.

00:58.564 --> 01:00.064
He doesn't want any presents.

01:00.166 --> 01:02.232
I'm just gonna defrost
that steak we got cheap

01:02.335 --> 01:04.134
at the Frugal Hoosier power-outage sale

01:04.159 --> 01:05.135
and leave him alone.

01:05.236 --> 01:06.270
He'll be happy.

01:06.295 --> 01:08.405
Okay, we can't just not do <i> anything.</i>

01:08.507 --> 01:10.741
He sold his diaper business
so I could go to school.

01:10.843 --> 01:12.286
Besides, when you're over 50,

01:12.311 --> 01:13.877
you have to cherish every birthday.

01:13.980 --> 01:15.279
What's that supposed to mean?

01:15.381 --> 01:17.681
- Nothing.
- I know what it means.

01:17.783 --> 01:19.760
Listen, where would
I have hidden something

01:19.785 --> 01:21.852
that I know I could find,
but nobody else would?

01:21.954 --> 01:23.520
The basement?

01:23.623 --> 01:25.556
No, I don't hide things in the basement.

01:25.658 --> 01:27.191
Or do I? [Sighs]

01:27.293 --> 01:28.726
Don't turn over 50.

01:28.828 --> 01:33.030
♪

01:33.132 --> 01:34.798
Hey, friend.

01:34.900 --> 01:36.467
[Sighs] Hi, Dylan.

01:36.569 --> 01:38.060
You're just gonna leave me hanging?

01:38.162 --> 01:39.670
Do we have to do this every day?

01:39.695 --> 01:40.848
I just want to get to class.

01:40.873 --> 01:42.083
What are you talking about?

01:42.108 --> 01:43.374
I'm just trying to greet my pal

01:43.399 --> 01:44.441
with a friendly handshake.

01:44.835 --> 01:46.500
You know we're not friends.

01:46.525 --> 01:48.712
Sure, we are. And what do friends do?

01:48.814 --> 01:50.514
They shake hands.

01:50.616 --> 01:52.383
I'll shake your hand.

01:53.185 --> 01:54.318
Yow!

01:54.420 --> 01:56.453
Leave my boyfriend alone.

01:58.524 --> 01:59.690
You're a weirdo.

02:00.991 --> 02:02.626
[School bell rings]

02:02.728 --> 02:04.995
[Gasps] Wow.

02:05.097 --> 02:06.130
Thanks.

02:06.232 --> 02:07.431
Let's go, Brick.

02:07.533 --> 02:09.366
Let me get that for you.

02:11.070 --> 02:12.436
[Grunts]

02:12.538 --> 02:15.572
♪

02:21.514 --> 02:22.579
Ah, there you are.

02:22.715 --> 02:23.681
Okay, listen.

02:23.783 --> 02:25.449
I'm making a video for Dad's birthday.

02:25.551 --> 02:27.551
Picture this... his nearest and dearest

02:27.576 --> 02:29.830
recounting fond memories
and funny stories

02:29.855 --> 02:32.222
all edited together
into a cherished keepsake

02:32.247 --> 02:34.391
he can watch for the rest of his life.

02:34.493 --> 02:36.026
[Laughs] I haven't even made it yet,

02:36.095 --> 02:37.461
and I can't wait to give it to him.

02:37.563 --> 02:38.829
Oh, he'll love it.

02:38.931 --> 02:40.431
Okay, do you remember when you were 5

02:40.533 --> 02:41.765
and you wanted to wear makeup

02:41.790 --> 02:43.901
so you colored in your eyelid
with permanent marker?

02:43.926 --> 02:45.769
That idea was 100 times better
than this one.

02:45.871 --> 02:46.875
[Scoffs]

02:46.900 --> 02:48.338
Okay, well, what are you
gonna get him that's so great?

02:48.441 --> 02:49.640
I'm not getting him anything.

02:49.665 --> 02:50.941
Every day, I give him the gift

02:50.966 --> 02:52.910
of being the only positive
reflection of his DNA.

02:52.935 --> 02:54.378
Okay, look, I'm doing this,

02:54.403 --> 02:56.814
so I need you to be camera-ready
tomorrow at 3:00.

02:56.916 --> 02:58.192
Study the questions.

02:58.217 --> 03:00.484
I don't want to hear any
"uhs" or "ums" or "whatevers."

03:00.553 --> 03:02.619
"If Dad was an animal,
which one would he be?"

03:02.644 --> 03:04.855
"Which one of Dad's plaid shirts
is my favorite,

03:04.880 --> 03:06.234
the dark blue or the light blue?"

03:06.259 --> 03:08.625
[Laughs] Yeah, I wanted to have
at least one funny question.

03:08.728 --> 03:10.127
Well, you didn't.

03:10.229 --> 03:11.195
Uh, what?

03:11.297 --> 03:12.629
♪

03:12.732 --> 03:13.664
[Exhales sharply]

03:13.766 --> 03:15.365
What's with you?

03:15.434 --> 03:16.500
Nothing.

03:16.569 --> 03:17.801
Good talk.

03:17.903 --> 03:19.136
All right, you dragged it out of me.

03:19.238 --> 03:20.604
It's something to do with Cindy.

03:20.639 --> 03:22.759
What? Did you lose the stepladder
you use to kiss her?

03:23.325 --> 03:24.318
Funny.

03:24.687 --> 03:27.038
You know, I've always
considered myself a modern man.

03:27.106 --> 03:29.336
I believe women's rights
are human rights, but...

03:29.405 --> 03:31.315
[Sighs]...today I was getting bullied.

03:31.417 --> 03:32.816
You were getting bullied?

03:32.918 --> 03:34.118
Are you okay?

03:34.186 --> 03:35.953
Do I need to step in and talk
some sense into this guy?

03:36.021 --> 03:37.020
No.

03:37.045 --> 03:38.455
Cindy chased him away.

03:39.525 --> 03:41.191
- Whoa.
- I know.

03:41.293 --> 03:42.993
Being bullied didn't bother me so much

03:43.062 --> 03:44.862
as having my girlfriend stick up for me.

03:44.930 --> 03:47.301
It made me feel... less than

03:47.327 --> 03:48.309
'cause Cindy's a girl,

03:48.334 --> 03:49.533
but it shouldn't have.

03:49.635 --> 03:50.701
No, it definitely should have.

03:50.770 --> 03:52.063
That is super embarrassing.

03:52.088 --> 03:53.303
Just tell me
it wasn't in front of people

03:53.372 --> 03:54.538
and they don't know you're a Heck.

03:54.640 --> 03:56.173
I mean, I could tell you that.

03:56.275 --> 03:57.107
I don't know.

03:57.176 --> 03:59.343
In the past, it's never bothered me

03:59.411 --> 04:01.512
to be the kid
who has to take a water break

04:01.614 --> 04:02.746
during the 50-yard dash

04:02.815 --> 04:05.282
or the guy at lunch
who can't open his own banana,

04:05.351 --> 04:07.217
but I'm having trouble
accepting the fact

04:07.286 --> 04:09.052
that my girlfriend is stronger than me.

04:09.121 --> 04:10.521
And I don't know what to do about it.

04:10.589 --> 04:11.955
I'm thinking I might need to get

04:11.991 --> 04:13.188
some of those muscles I've read about.

04:13.213 --> 04:16.527
Mm. Well, it just so happens,
I can help you with that.

04:16.629 --> 04:17.798
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

04:17.867 --> 04:19.428
I'll whip you into shape in no time.

04:19.498 --> 04:21.531
We just got to gauge
your starting point,

04:21.600 --> 04:23.433
so, uh, let's get a banana in here.

04:23.536 --> 04:25.002
[Chuckles]

04:25.037 --> 04:26.737
But seriously, we should get a banana.

04:26.839 --> 04:28.405
[Gasps]

04:28.507 --> 04:30.507
♪

04:30.609 --> 04:31.875
Mom, are you okay?

04:31.944 --> 04:33.143
Shh.

04:33.212 --> 04:34.144
I'm trying to picture

04:34.213 --> 04:35.846
the last place I saw Axl's present.

04:35.948 --> 04:37.781
And also what it was.

04:37.850 --> 04:40.818
Okay, but did you get my e-mail?

04:41.355 --> 04:42.652
The subject line was,

04:42.677 --> 04:44.888
"Super Top Secret
Do Not Open in Front of Dad."

04:44.990 --> 04:47.024
I don't read all your e-mails, Sue.

04:47.126 --> 04:48.258
You e-mail me a lot.

04:48.327 --> 04:50.227
Well, I need you
to read over these questions

04:50.296 --> 04:52.572
- before I film you tomorrow.
- Film me?

04:52.597 --> 04:54.097
Wait, what exactly are you doing?

04:54.200 --> 04:55.999
I thought you were making him

04:56.068 --> 04:58.101
a glitter card or glitter cookies.

04:58.204 --> 04:59.903
- You're so good with glitter.
- No.

05:00.005 --> 05:01.038
I'm making him a video

05:01.106 --> 05:02.973
of people saying nice things about Dad.

05:03.042 --> 05:05.709
Oh, Sue, he's gonna hate that.

05:05.744 --> 05:07.845
- What? No, he's gonna love it.
- [Sighs]

05:07.913 --> 05:09.546
I know he acts like a tough guy,

05:09.648 --> 05:11.448
but he's got the squooshiest center.

05:11.517 --> 05:13.283
You didn't see him at "Moana." I did.

05:13.385 --> 05:16.053
Look, I've known your dad
for over 20 years.

05:16.155 --> 05:17.988
There's no squoosh in there.

05:18.057 --> 05:19.489
Well, there is definitely
gonna be some softening

05:19.592 --> 05:20.591
after this video.

05:20.659 --> 05:22.259
I can promise you that.

05:22.328 --> 05:23.994
Now, I need you
to read over these questions.

05:24.096 --> 05:24.995
I am counting on you

05:25.064 --> 05:27.331
for all the emotional tender stuff.

05:27.433 --> 05:29.600
[Scoffs] I can't even find the present.

05:29.635 --> 05:31.668
How am I supposed to remember
why I used to love your dad?

05:31.737 --> 05:32.736
[Inhales sharply]

05:32.838 --> 05:36.206
♪

05:36.275 --> 05:37.674
Okay, got everything
you need right here...

05:37.776 --> 05:40.110
bench, curls, squats.

05:40.179 --> 05:41.560
But our first exercise...

05:42.888 --> 05:44.060
...notebook toss.

05:44.128 --> 05:45.610
Brick, you don't got to be writing it.

05:45.635 --> 05:46.483
We're gonna be doing it.

05:46.552 --> 05:48.785
I thought there was gonna be
a learning portion first.

05:48.888 --> 05:49.953
I don't need to be a hero.

05:50.022 --> 05:51.221
There's no danger of that.

05:51.323 --> 05:53.090
Now, let me show you
what you're aiming for here.

05:53.192 --> 05:54.491
Ahhh.

05:54.894 --> 05:56.560
Oof.

05:56.662 --> 05:58.061
[Spits]

05:58.998 --> 05:59.930
Huh?

06:00.032 --> 06:01.598
[Grunts]

06:06.338 --> 06:08.205
[Panting]

06:08.307 --> 06:09.673
Must be a little rusty.

06:09.775 --> 06:11.174
I haven't been training.

06:11.243 --> 06:13.410
I kind of shut the gun show down
after football ended.

06:13.479 --> 06:15.045
[Exhales sharply]

06:15.147 --> 06:16.413
[Grunts]

06:16.515 --> 06:17.814
Oh, no.

06:17.917 --> 06:19.316
Oh, God.

06:19.418 --> 06:20.984
I don't think this floor is level.

06:21.086 --> 06:22.686
[Grunts, groans]

06:22.788 --> 06:23.820
[Sighs heavily]

06:24.490 --> 06:25.756
[Exhales]

06:25.824 --> 06:27.457
[Grunts]

06:27.559 --> 06:28.992
Notice how straight I'm keeping my body.

06:29.094 --> 06:32.095
Arms parallel.

06:32.164 --> 06:35.832
[Grunts]

06:35.935 --> 06:39.102
Always... maintain...

06:39.204 --> 06:40.570
- [Crashing]
- ...proper form.

06:40.673 --> 06:41.905
I'll pick those up.

06:42.007 --> 06:46.240
[Panting]

06:46.342 --> 06:47.711
So...

06:47.813 --> 06:49.813
how many of those should I do?

06:51.969 --> 06:54.366
I remember the time
Dad took me to play tennis.

06:54.577 --> 06:55.820
He got mad 'cause I brought my books,

06:55.845 --> 06:58.251
which the veins in his neck
start popping out, but...

06:58.287 --> 06:59.258
Sue: Cut.

06:59.327 --> 07:00.984
Brick, these are supposed to be
nice memories.

07:00.984 --> 07:02.317
Uh, that is a nice memory.

07:02.386 --> 07:03.806
Dad and I don't do a lot together.

07:03.831 --> 07:05.200
Okay, well, it doesn't sound so nice.

07:05.269 --> 07:07.188
Now I want heartfelt, so step it up.

07:07.291 --> 07:08.790
Okay, make me feel something.

07:08.859 --> 07:10.926
And... action.

07:11.581 --> 07:13.195
Here's a fond memory with Dad...

07:13.263 --> 07:15.063
the time he tried
to teach me how to drive.

07:15.132 --> 07:16.965
The veins were really
popping out of his neck then.

07:17.034 --> 07:19.034
Brick, stop talking about veins.

07:19.102 --> 07:20.936
Oh, all right, fine. Sorry.

07:21.038 --> 07:23.972
Um, let's see.

07:24.041 --> 07:26.141
Well, one of my best times with Dad

07:26.209 --> 07:28.209
was when he had me rake leaves.

07:28.278 --> 07:31.146
It was funny 'cause
I was probably 9 at the time,

07:31.214 --> 07:33.134
and I was worried about
the leaves being incinerated...

07:33.174 --> 07:34.552
Cut.

07:34.588 --> 07:37.118
Mom, I was finally getting
something good out of Brick,

07:37.187 --> 07:38.653
and you're ruining my shot.

07:38.755 --> 07:39.688
I am so close.

07:39.756 --> 07:41.890
You can film Dad's thing anywhere.

07:41.992 --> 07:42.891
Shh.

07:42.960 --> 07:43.992
I don't want to spoil the surprise.

07:44.061 --> 07:44.960
It's a secret.

07:45.028 --> 07:46.414
Here's something that's not a secret.

07:46.439 --> 07:47.741
Dad's gonna hate this video.

07:47.766 --> 07:49.264
Okay, from other people,
he might hate it,

07:49.289 --> 07:50.565
but not from me.

07:50.590 --> 07:52.276
Now, Mom, will you please
get out of my shot?

07:52.301 --> 07:54.703
I finally had a vein-free story
from Brick,

07:54.728 --> 07:55.770
and you screwed it up.

07:55.795 --> 07:56.736
That's actually not true.

07:56.761 --> 07:58.873
The end of the story comes
around nicely back to veins.

07:58.942 --> 08:00.675
- Brick.
- [Gasps] Yes!

08:00.744 --> 08:02.477
Ha-ha! This is it.

08:02.546 --> 08:03.845
Now I remember.

08:03.947 --> 08:05.080
I was at the doughnut shop,

08:05.148 --> 08:07.048
and this new store, The Giftery,
had opened next door.

08:07.117 --> 08:09.184
I was in there killing time,

08:09.252 --> 08:13.388
when I came across
this absolutely perfect...

08:13.490 --> 08:14.522
Shoe horn?

08:14.624 --> 08:17.559
No, no, no, it's not just a shoe horn.

08:17.594 --> 08:20.718
It's the "Busy Businessman's
Luxury Shoe Care Kit."

08:21.398 --> 08:23.164
Oh, yeah, get it?

08:23.200 --> 08:24.866
'Cause Axl's a business major.

08:24.901 --> 08:27.002
I remember thinking
this would be symbolic

08:27.104 --> 08:28.236
for when he gets a job.

08:28.305 --> 08:31.468
I mean, it's got polish
and a little applicator,

08:31.536 --> 08:33.707
and it comes in
this handy carrying case.

08:33.744 --> 08:35.043
Yeah, this sucks.

08:35.111 --> 08:36.169
Ugh, crap.

08:36.201 --> 08:37.979
Now I got to get him something else.

08:38.048 --> 08:40.948
Oh, well, at least I got him
a cute card a while ago.

08:44.054 --> 08:45.854
♪

08:45.956 --> 08:47.055
Okay.

08:47.157 --> 08:48.923
Frankie: <i>So we celebrated
Mike's birthday</i>

08:49.026 --> 08:50.425
<i>just the way he wanted...</i>

08:50.460 --> 08:51.760
<i>I defrosted a steak,</i>

08:51.785 --> 08:53.862
<i>and he got to read</i>
Sports Illustrated <i> at the table</i>

08:53.930 --> 08:55.497
<i>while the rest of us didn't talk.</i>

08:55.599 --> 08:56.998
Okay.

08:57.067 --> 08:58.166
You can speak.

08:58.268 --> 08:59.801
Happy birthday, Dad. [Squeals]

08:59.903 --> 09:01.436
- All righty.
- Wait, wait, wait.

09:01.461 --> 09:02.837
I got you a present.

09:02.906 --> 09:03.905
You did? What for?

09:04.007 --> 09:05.408
I told you I didn't want anything.

09:05.477 --> 09:07.042
And that's why
I didn't get you anything.

09:07.110 --> 09:08.109
You're welcome, Dad.

09:08.211 --> 09:09.411
Consider Father's Day forgotten, too.

09:09.479 --> 09:10.979
You're a good son.

09:11.048 --> 09:12.814
Are you seriously gonna argue with me?

09:12.916 --> 09:14.549
Just take it, you big party pooper.

09:14.651 --> 09:15.739
Happy birthday.

09:15.841 --> 09:17.585
Okay.

09:17.687 --> 09:19.054
It is a gift.

09:19.156 --> 09:20.288
You open it.

09:23.400 --> 09:24.992
Mm.

09:27.456 --> 09:31.057
The "Busy Business Man's
Luxury Shoe Care Kit."

09:31.159 --> 09:33.293
Ha! That sucks.

09:33.395 --> 09:34.961
I love it.

09:35.030 --> 09:36.863
Did you keep the receipt?

09:36.932 --> 09:37.997
No, wait, wait, wait.

09:38.066 --> 09:39.808
I haven't given you my gift yet.

09:39.910 --> 09:41.717
But mine isn't something
that can be opened.

09:41.742 --> 09:43.369
It must be experienced.

09:43.438 --> 09:44.971
So if you would all be so kind

09:45.040 --> 09:46.873
as to follow me to the family room.

09:48.016 --> 09:49.716
Leave the magazine.

09:49.741 --> 09:51.711
♪

09:51.780 --> 09:52.946
[Sighs] Okay.

09:52.971 --> 09:55.515
Now if you would all focus
your attention to the TV.

09:55.617 --> 09:56.850
Mike: That I can do.

09:57.255 --> 10:00.520
Sue Sue Heck Productions
proudly presents...

10:03.258 --> 10:05.658
[ <i> Up-tempo music plays</i> ]

10:05.694 --> 10:07.691
<i>Good evening. I'm Sue Heck.</i>

10:07.724 --> 10:09.863
<i>And this is a celebration
of Michael Heck.</i>

10:09.965 --> 10:10.897
[ <i> Popping</i> ]

10:10.999 --> 10:11.765
[ <i> Ding!</i> ]

10:11.833 --> 10:14.934
<i>It all began here in 1963,</i>

10:15.036 --> 10:16.703
<i>the year this wonderful man,</i>

10:16.772 --> 10:18.772
<i>a man who means so much to the world,</i>

10:18.807 --> 10:20.039
<i>was born.</i>

10:20.142 --> 10:22.342
- [ <i> Baby cries</i> ]
- Sue: [Chuckles]

10:22.444 --> 10:23.877
I couldn't find a baby picture of you.

10:23.945 --> 10:26.079
<i>So what makes a man great?</i>

10:26.181 --> 10:27.814
<i>Let's find out, shall we?</i>

10:27.883 --> 10:29.215
<i>What do I love about Mike?</i>

10:29.284 --> 10:31.751
<i>Uh, well, obviously, I love him
'cause I married him.</i>

10:31.853 --> 10:33.920
<i>And, um, what else?</i>

10:34.022 --> 10:35.221
<i>Well, he's a great provider.</i>

10:35.290 --> 10:36.990
<i>Yeah, I would say he's my rock.</i>

10:37.092 --> 10:38.124
[ <i> Clang</i> ]

10:38.226 --> 10:40.527
<i>Happy B to the Big M from the Big A.</i>

10:40.595 --> 10:42.162
<i>Wait, that sounds bathroom-y.
Can I start over?</i>

10:42.230 --> 10:43.897
<i>The cool about thing about Dad</i>

10:43.999 --> 10:46.166
<i>is his hair looks the same wet or dry.</i>

10:46.234 --> 10:48.902
<i>He's... my rock.</i>

10:49.004 --> 10:50.181
<i>Oh, I said that already?</i>

10:50.238 --> 10:51.261
<i>Pbht.</i>

10:51.287 --> 10:53.773
<i>Uh, if Dad were a spice,</i>

10:53.875 --> 10:56.976
<i>uh, I'd say he's salt.</i>

10:57.045 --> 10:58.444
<i>Old Spice.</i>

10:58.513 --> 11:00.180
- [Both laugh]
- Brick: <i> Is beer a spice?</i>

11:00.282 --> 11:01.915
<i>'Cause, if so, I'd say beer.</i>

11:02.017 --> 11:03.449
<i>When there's no beer in the house,</i>

11:03.518 --> 11:04.851
<i>he gets tense, and this vein...</i>

11:04.920 --> 11:07.287
<i>Mike, I didn't know
it was your birthday.</i>

11:07.322 --> 11:09.189
<i>You're just full of secrets, aren't you?</i>

11:09.291 --> 11:11.658
Wait. This isn't just family.

11:11.760 --> 11:13.092
Nope.

11:13.161 --> 11:14.327
<i>Well, we're gonna have to have
you over for dinner.</i>

11:14.429 --> 11:15.428
<i>When's good for you?</i>

11:15.463 --> 11:16.663
<i>How's this Tuesday?</i>

11:16.731 --> 11:19.032
<i>Ron! Mike's coming over
for dinner on Tuesday.</i>

11:19.067 --> 11:21.501
<i>Three words that describe Mike?</i>

11:21.570 --> 11:24.512
<i>Only three? Oh, gosh, that's hard.</i>

11:24.614 --> 11:27.515
<i>Hero, gentle giant...</i>

11:27.584 --> 11:29.117
<i>shoot, that's already three.</i>

11:29.186 --> 11:30.451
<i>Can I have one more?</i>

11:30.520 --> 11:32.220
<i>Which Mike? I got five Mikes.</i>

11:32.289 --> 11:34.522
- Sue: [Laughs]
- You talked to my barber?

11:34.624 --> 11:35.642
[Laughing] Yeah.

11:35.667 --> 11:37.317
<i>Tall Mike... got to put the chair</i>

11:37.419 --> 11:39.152
<i>all the way down when he comes in.</i>

11:39.254 --> 11:41.888
<i>If Mike were a flavor of ice cream,</i>

11:41.990 --> 11:44.757
<i>he'd be... vanilla.</i>

11:44.860 --> 11:45.458
<i>Vanilla.</i>

11:45.527 --> 11:46.526
<i>Vanilla, clearly.</i>

11:46.628 --> 11:47.260
<i>Vanilla.</i>

11:47.329 --> 11:47.927
<i>Vanilla.</i>

11:48.029 --> 11:50.630
<i>Show me vanilla!</i>

11:50.699 --> 11:52.332
George: <i>Uh, I'm based
in the corporate office,</i>

11:52.400 --> 11:55.268
<i>so I don't really
know Mike Heck that well,</i>

11:55.370 --> 11:56.569
<i>which kind of makes it hard for me</i>

11:56.671 --> 11:59.305
<i>to share my favorite, uh, "Mike moment."</i>

11:59.407 --> 12:01.441
Sue, that's my boss.

12:01.509 --> 12:02.575
Surprise.

12:02.677 --> 12:04.510
<i>My favorite Mike moment is,</i>

12:04.613 --> 12:07.080
<i>sometimes, when he's
getting out of his car,</i>

12:07.148 --> 12:08.770
<i>he pretends like he doesn't hear me</i>

12:08.795 --> 12:09.956
<i>calling from my yard,</i>

12:09.981 --> 12:12.085
<i>and he just walks into his house.</i>

12:12.187 --> 12:13.753
[ <i> Laughs</i> ] <i> Hilarious.</i>

12:13.855 --> 12:17.190
<i>I have so many Mike moments,
it's hard to pick.</i>

12:17.292 --> 12:18.958
<i>Well, not a lot of people know this,</i>

12:19.060 --> 12:20.727
<i>but Mike loves cats.</i>

12:20.762 --> 12:23.696
<i>One time, I came
into the trailer on a break,</i>

12:23.798 --> 12:25.373
<i>and Mike was watching this video</i>

12:25.442 --> 12:27.200
<i>of kittens befriending a bunny rabbit.</i>

12:27.302 --> 12:29.302
Okay, that's enough.

12:29.404 --> 12:31.537
- [Video fast forwards]
- I get the gist.

12:31.640 --> 12:32.839
Wait, wait, wait. No, no, no.

12:32.941 --> 12:34.707
Uh, there's, like, 15 more minutes left.

12:34.809 --> 12:36.542
Brad does a special poem,

12:36.611 --> 12:37.944
and the bagger at Frugal Hoosier

12:38.046 --> 12:39.512
had a really funny story.

12:39.614 --> 12:40.813
You're gonna miss it.

12:40.916 --> 12:41.814
Yeah, well.

12:41.917 --> 12:45.685
♪

12:45.787 --> 12:46.753
Here you go.

12:46.855 --> 12:48.221
What do you want me to do with this?

12:48.323 --> 12:52.625
♪

12:52.727 --> 12:54.460
Well, the shoe kit's looking better.

12:54.562 --> 12:56.229
♪

13:01.232 --> 13:02.565
What is the matter with you?

13:02.633 --> 13:03.699
I'm sorry.

13:03.735 --> 13:05.968
I just don't like people
making a big deal over me

13:06.037 --> 13:08.571
or talking about me
or thinking about me.

13:08.606 --> 13:09.538
Now I got to get a new barber,

13:09.607 --> 13:10.673
and I liked this guy, too.

13:10.742 --> 13:12.608
I'd just gotten him
to stop making small talk.

13:12.685 --> 13:14.118
Okay, I know I'm married to a man

13:14.178 --> 13:16.053
with the emotional capacity
of a garden gnome,

13:16.155 --> 13:17.555
so I'm used to the disappointment.

13:17.657 --> 13:19.123
But Sue isn't.

13:19.192 --> 13:20.491
She's really hurting.

13:20.526 --> 13:22.193
Ah, she didn't look that upset.

13:22.295 --> 13:23.427
[Scoffs]

13:23.496 --> 13:25.162
Because she was pretending
everything was okay

13:25.231 --> 13:26.430
for <i> your</i> sake,

13:26.499 --> 13:28.432
which is what you should have
been doing for her.

13:28.501 --> 13:30.630
Oh, you're just being dramatic.
She's fine.

13:31.337 --> 13:34.305
And just to be clear,
that kitten video...

13:34.373 --> 13:35.306
that just popped up

13:35.374 --> 13:36.757
when I was researching granite prices,

13:36.825 --> 13:39.043
so we're not gonna go
sharing that with anybody.

13:39.145 --> 13:40.444
♪

13:40.480 --> 13:42.880
Frankie: <i>So Mike was positive
that Sue was fine,</i>

13:42.949 --> 13:45.649
<i>but after having a little time
to think it over...</i>

13:46.486 --> 13:47.485
Sue.

13:47.553 --> 13:48.752
Sue: Yeah?

13:48.855 --> 13:50.988
Sorry.

13:51.057 --> 13:52.189
Okay.

13:52.258 --> 13:55.192
♪

13:59.190 --> 14:00.422
What are you doing?

14:00.491 --> 14:02.491
Nothing, nothing.
Just admiring the view.

14:02.527 --> 14:04.093
How are those workouts coming?

14:04.162 --> 14:05.928
Well, I know I need to get in shape,

14:05.997 --> 14:08.164
so I did the only thing
that made sense to me.

14:08.232 --> 14:10.274
I went to the library
and checked out a book.

14:10.343 --> 14:12.001
Jack Lalanne's "Live Young Forever."

14:12.103 --> 14:14.503
- Oh, okay. What's he doing now?
- He's dead.

14:14.572 --> 14:16.505
But before that, he was really cool.

14:16.607 --> 14:18.242
He could lift all these heavy things.

14:18.267 --> 14:20.251
He once pulled 70 boats.

14:20.353 --> 14:21.510
My goal is 15.

14:21.579 --> 14:23.012
That should be enough to impress Cindy.

14:23.047 --> 14:24.513
Look, Brick, you don't need a book.

14:24.615 --> 14:25.648
You got me as your trainer.

14:25.750 --> 14:27.200
No offense, Axl,

14:27.225 --> 14:29.985
but things weren't really
going that well in the garage.

14:30.054 --> 14:31.187
It's been two days,

14:31.255 --> 14:33.122
and I think I might have
actually lost muscle mass.

14:33.191 --> 14:35.257
That's just all
part of the workout program

14:35.359 --> 14:37.326
I've created specifically for your body.

14:37.395 --> 14:38.994
Right now you're like a lump of clay,

14:39.096 --> 14:40.129
but you give me some time,

14:40.198 --> 14:42.031
I'm gonna mold you
into a work of fine art.

14:42.099 --> 14:43.499
It's like the statue of David.

14:43.534 --> 14:45.534
You think Michael and Angelo
sculpted that thing overnight?

14:45.636 --> 14:46.569
No.

14:46.671 --> 14:48.504
Took those guys years.

14:48.573 --> 14:50.072
Yeah...

14:50.141 --> 14:52.608
I just don't think someone
who's on the decline physically

14:52.677 --> 14:53.709
should be teaching me.

14:53.778 --> 14:54.476
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

14:54.579 --> 14:55.845
Decline? [Laughs]

14:55.947 --> 14:57.146
Decli... wha...?

14:57.181 --> 14:58.848
Who said I'm declining?
I'm not declining.

14:58.950 --> 15:00.416
Look, it's perfectly natural.

15:00.484 --> 15:01.650
In my research,

15:01.719 --> 15:03.686
I found that men hit their
physical peak at age 25,

15:03.788 --> 15:05.120
then slowly decline.

15:05.189 --> 15:06.555
You're just a little ahead of schedule.

15:06.657 --> 15:07.656
From here on out,

15:07.758 --> 15:08.691
you're pretty much just gonna atrophy.

15:08.793 --> 15:10.234
Got enough trophies, Brick.

15:10.302 --> 15:12.069
And, yeah, maybe
I let myself go a little bit,

15:12.138 --> 15:13.696
but I just got to do a few pushups,

15:13.764 --> 15:15.172
I'll be back in shape like that.

15:15.274 --> 15:16.473
Ow, cramp.

15:16.576 --> 15:19.101
♪

15:19.203 --> 15:20.436
[ <i> Laughter on TV</i> ]

15:20.538 --> 15:21.437
Come on.

15:21.539 --> 15:22.605
Where are we going?

15:22.673 --> 15:24.139
Ice cream. Let's go.

15:24.870 --> 15:26.217
No, thanks.

15:27.178 --> 15:28.277
My treat.

15:28.379 --> 15:29.578
You're gonna want to be there.

15:29.647 --> 15:31.513
I'm thinking of ordering
something besides vanilla.

15:31.850 --> 15:33.983
It's all right. I'm not hungry.

15:34.051 --> 15:38.153
[ <i> Laughter on TV</i> ]

15:38.222 --> 15:40.823
♪

15:40.892 --> 15:43.392
<i>The next day, Axl was still
bugged by what Brick said.</i>

15:43.427 --> 15:45.628
<i>I mean, if Jack Lalanne
could pull 70 boats,</i>

15:45.730 --> 15:47.663
<i>surely there's something he could do.</i>

15:47.765 --> 15:50.866
♪

15:50.968 --> 15:53.669
[Exhales]

15:53.738 --> 15:55.871
[Grunts]

15:55.907 --> 15:57.973
[Panting]

15:58.075 --> 15:59.308
You're a man. You're a man.

15:59.377 --> 16:00.943
You're a big, strong man. [Grunts]

16:01.045 --> 16:02.211
Axl: Aah!

16:02.413 --> 16:03.779
[Groans]

16:10.721 --> 16:12.187
I don't want to talk about it, Brick.

16:12.256 --> 16:13.756
We're never mentioning this ever again.

16:13.858 --> 16:14.690
No one needs to know

16:14.759 --> 16:15.991
I only moved the 'Bago two feet.

16:16.060 --> 16:17.159
You didn't move it at all.

16:17.261 --> 16:18.260
You're mean.

16:18.362 --> 16:19.728
This isn't fair.

16:19.830 --> 16:21.130
Used to be, I was feeling weak,

16:21.198 --> 16:23.307
I'd just do a couple of pushups
and get my strength right back,

16:23.376 --> 16:24.775
but, my God, what is happening to me?

16:24.844 --> 16:27.102
You think it was all those
Froot Loop sandwiches?

16:27.952 --> 16:29.293
Oh, God.

16:29.573 --> 16:31.140
[Scoffs] Froot Loop sandwiches.

16:35.012 --> 16:36.720
Don't look at my big butt.

16:36.789 --> 16:38.922
Axl, get a hold of yourself.

16:38.991 --> 16:40.382
I got rescued by my girlfriend,

16:40.451 --> 16:41.884
and even I'm embarrassed for you.

16:41.986 --> 16:44.853
Look, I'm about to graduate.

16:44.889 --> 16:46.822
Pretty soon, I'm gonna be
sitting at a desk all day

16:46.891 --> 16:48.666
doing whatever it is
I'm supposed to be doing,

16:48.734 --> 16:49.700
and I'm just gonna decay.

16:49.769 --> 16:52.903
I am one step closer
to becoming Mom and Dad.

16:52.972 --> 16:55.172
Hey, there's a silver lining in this.

16:55.241 --> 16:58.542
Yes, men peak physically
in their mid-20s,

16:58.611 --> 17:01.445
but they don't peak mentally
till age 35.

17:01.547 --> 17:02.538
You're still in the upswing.

17:02.640 --> 17:05.140
Mental's never really been
my strong suit.

17:05.209 --> 17:08.109
Well, it just so happens
I can help you with that.

17:08.511 --> 17:09.920
- Really?
- Yep.

17:09.989 --> 17:11.623
By the time I'm done with you,

17:11.691 --> 17:14.215
your brain is gonna be ripped.

17:14.318 --> 17:17.575
Now, let's start with PBS.

17:17.599 --> 17:18.633
Ugh.

17:19.056 --> 17:20.823
This is gonna be so hard.

17:20.891 --> 17:23.425
- Got to put in the work.
- [Sighs]

17:23.450 --> 17:25.294
Oh, and by the way,

17:25.363 --> 17:29.064
Michael and Angelo... one guy.

17:29.166 --> 17:30.099
What?

17:30.201 --> 17:36.238
♪

17:36.307 --> 17:38.666
I hope it's okay
I'm driving you back to school.

17:39.377 --> 17:41.377
Mom was gonna, but she's busy,

17:41.479 --> 17:43.278
and I got nothing going on.

17:43.381 --> 17:44.778
It's fine.

17:46.017 --> 17:47.883
Thank you.

17:47.985 --> 17:49.018
What?

17:49.120 --> 17:50.986
You know, for the, uh,
whole video thing.

17:51.088 --> 17:52.454
That was nice.

17:52.556 --> 17:53.822
Okay.

17:56.627 --> 17:57.826
I don't get it.

17:57.895 --> 17:59.828
I said, "Thank you,"
I said, "I'm sorry,"

17:59.930 --> 18:01.096
I said, "Ice cream,"

18:01.198 --> 18:03.465
and nothing's sticking.

18:03.534 --> 18:04.566
I'm trying,

18:04.602 --> 18:05.567
but I'm not getting any traction here.

18:05.669 --> 18:07.803
It's like I'm talking to your mom.

18:07.905 --> 18:09.538
It's all right, Dad.

18:09.607 --> 18:10.939
I'm really not that upset.

18:11.008 --> 18:13.745
I know that's just how you are.

18:14.678 --> 18:16.011
[Sighs]

18:16.113 --> 18:17.946
Look, growing up in my family,

18:18.015 --> 18:22.885
we didn't, you know, talk
or, you know, express things

18:22.920 --> 18:25.475
on birthdays or holidays or...

18:26.257 --> 18:28.057
Even when my Mom died,

18:28.675 --> 18:30.459
I came home from basketball
practice one day,

18:30.528 --> 18:33.566
and my dad said, "Your mom passed."

18:34.298 --> 18:36.532
Then he told me to go do my homework.

18:37.027 --> 18:38.901
The next morning, I went to school.

18:39.923 --> 18:42.071
We never talked about it again.

18:42.691 --> 18:44.006
Really?

18:44.075 --> 18:45.707
Oh, my gosh, that's horrible.

18:46.844 --> 18:48.617
It's just the way it was.

18:51.949 --> 18:54.583
Well, you're not like that, you know.

18:54.652 --> 18:56.718
I mean, you're way better than Grandpa.

18:56.821 --> 18:58.687
When I try to hug him, he just says,

18:58.789 --> 19:00.622
"Oh, you don't want to hug an old man."

19:00.724 --> 19:02.825
But you tolerate my hugs all the time.

19:02.893 --> 19:04.793
Well, he cares about you.

19:04.895 --> 19:06.628
He's just not real comfortable
saying it.

19:08.466 --> 19:10.374
We all do. Care about you.

19:12.036 --> 19:13.402
I know.

19:16.715 --> 19:18.574
How did she die again?

19:19.811 --> 19:21.877
Lung cancer.

19:22.947 --> 19:25.915
She was young, just 42.

19:26.951 --> 19:29.593
But the way she used to
dance around the house,

19:29.695 --> 19:31.595
you'd have thought she was 20.

19:31.697 --> 19:35.379
She was always singing, always moving.

19:36.227 --> 19:38.327
I can still see her at the kitchen sink

19:38.429 --> 19:40.859
doing dishes and humming to herself.

19:41.599 --> 19:43.328
When I'd be playing in the kitchen,

19:43.890 --> 19:44.922
she'd call me over

19:44.947 --> 19:47.202
and scoop some soap suds in her hands

19:47.304 --> 19:49.938
and bend down
and let me blow the bubbles.

19:50.040 --> 19:52.452
Aww. I wish I had met her.

19:52.477 --> 19:54.109
Yeah.

19:54.211 --> 19:56.111
Well, you'd have liked her.
She was nice.

19:57.748 --> 19:59.815
- She was a teacher, right?
- Mm-hmm.

19:59.917 --> 20:02.243
Third grade and then fifth.

20:03.821 --> 20:06.288
Once, when she was working
as a substitute,

20:06.390 --> 20:08.857
- she actually taught my class.
- [Gasps]

20:08.959 --> 20:10.959
I was sitting there and in walks my mom.

20:11.061 --> 20:12.127
[Laughs]

20:12.229 --> 20:13.262
Classic.

20:13.364 --> 20:14.563
[Both laugh]

20:15.891 --> 20:20.897
♪

20:20.998 --> 20:21.997
Unh-unh, unh-unh.

20:22.099 --> 20:23.599
I've been doing a little work on myself.

20:23.701 --> 20:25.734
I can get this for m'lady.

20:32.776 --> 20:34.476
[Grunts]

20:34.578 --> 20:35.878
Okay.

20:37.248 --> 20:38.947
Actually, that's a little too heavy.

20:43.921 --> 20:45.554
Yeah.

20:45.623 --> 20:46.989
Yeah, I've been doing some lifting.

20:47.091 --> 20:49.091
- Weights?
- No, books.

20:49.193 --> 20:51.526
I started with Jack Lalanne's
"Live Young Forever,"

20:51.629 --> 20:53.829
but I'm thinking about
upgrading to an encyclopedia

20:53.931 --> 20:55.430
or maybe even an almanac.

20:55.532 --> 20:57.733
♪
